<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-06T05:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-09-27T04:00:00-05:00" n="471" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3523: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1920-10-06T06:34:00-04:00" notBefore="1920-09-27T17:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>].<lb/>[Received October 6,
                                    1920—6:34 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>297. Following telegram has been received from Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“September 27, 5 p.m. General Lee Fu Lin, commander of troops
                                        Island of Honam opposite Canton, and General Wei Pang Ping,
                                        commissioner of defense Canton, having together about 6,000
                                        troops, have rebelled against the military government and
                                        threatening to attack Military Governor Mo unless he resigns
                                        and leaves Canton. Mo having but 6,000 troops at Canton is
                                        now discussing terms. Situation critical but foreigners
                                        amply protected. Two American and three British gunboats and
                                        two Japanese destroyers off Shameen. Kindly inform the
                                        consuls adding that I have delayed taking leave. Bergholz
                                        ”</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>